00:05:53.580 --> 00:05:58.860
So now let's turn to the whole
underpinning of 3.091.

00:05:58.860 --> 00:06:02.010
If we take a look at the
performance of any engineering

00:06:02.010 --> 00:06:04.990
system it's a combination
of the design and the

00:06:04.990 --> 00:06:06.480
construction.

00:06:06.480 --> 00:06:09.270
Now the construction is both the
workmanship and the choice

00:06:09.270 --> 00:06:10.060
of materials.

00:06:10.060 --> 00:06:11.630
Now how do we choose
materials?

00:06:11.630 --> 00:06:14.350
We choose them on the basis
of their properties.

00:06:14.350 --> 00:06:16.040
So, for example, here's an

00:06:16.040 --> 00:06:18.030
application: a beverage container.

00:06:18.030 --> 00:06:21.520
This one I'm holding is made
out of an aluminum alloy.

00:06:21.520 --> 00:06:22.910
It's a metal.

00:06:22.910 --> 00:06:25.540
When I was your age, they
had steel beverage cans.

00:06:25.540 --> 00:06:28.340
You can take this same beverage
and contain it in a

00:06:28.340 --> 00:06:30.190
glass bottle.

00:06:30.190 --> 00:06:35.790
You can contain it in
a polymer bottle.

00:06:35.790 --> 00:06:37.530
Why do we make those
various choices?

00:06:37.530 --> 00:06:40.040
Because they have the right
mix of properties.

00:06:40.040 --> 00:06:42.040
Now how do you determine
the properties?

00:06:42.040 --> 00:06:45.582
Properties obviously are
determined by the composition.

00:06:45.582 --> 00:06:50.050
We wouldn't make this thing
out of sodium chloride.

00:06:50.050 --> 00:06:52.080
It would dissolve.

00:06:52.080 --> 00:06:54.580
So composition is important,
but atomic arrangement is

00:06:54.580 --> 00:06:56.090
important as well.

00:06:56.090 --> 00:07:02.350
Example is 1/2-inch-thick
pine board compared to a

00:07:02.350 --> 00:07:05.210
1/2-inch-thick piece
of plywood.

00:07:05.210 --> 00:07:08.280
Both pine, but the
1/2-inch-thick pine board is

00:07:08.280 --> 00:07:10.250
one solid pine board.

00:07:10.250 --> 00:07:13.720
I can take that pine board and
I can fracture it if I strike

00:07:13.720 --> 00:07:15.150
it along the grain.

00:07:15.150 --> 00:07:17.510
But the 1/2-inch-thick plywood,
I can't do that

00:07:17.510 --> 00:07:22.610
because it's 1/8-inch sheet
pine cross-laminated.

00:07:22.610 --> 00:07:32.820
1/8 inch north-south, 1/8 inch
east-west. If I try to cut

00:07:32.820 --> 00:07:37.260
through that board, I can't
advance the fracture.

00:07:37.260 --> 00:07:40.350
Same composition, different
atomic arrangement.

00:07:40.350 --> 00:07:44.475
So the thesis of 3.091 is that
the electronic structure of

00:07:44.475 --> 00:07:47.590
the elements holds the key
to understanding that

00:07:47.590 --> 00:07:50.510
relationship between
composition, atomic

00:07:50.510 --> 00:07:51.730
arrangement, and properties.

00:07:51.730 --> 00:07:53.000
And once you have properties
that's how

00:07:53.000 --> 00:07:54.210
you make your selection.

00:07:54.210 --> 00:07:54.910
And away we go.

